Police are holding a 26-year-old man from Mulot, Bomet county, for allegedly withdrawing more than Sh400,000 from different Equity bank accounts. Peter Cheruiyot was arrested on Wednesday following fraud cases reported at several police stations from the last week. Detectives in Bomet confiscated several phones and ID cards during an operation in his home. The suspect is being interrogated as investigations continue. Police stations that had received complaints relating to fraud have been asked to liase with Bomet DCI. Last month,Â  Sh72 million was stolen from the Standard Chartered Bank and G4S in Nairobi by people posing as police officials. G4S officials told investigating officers that the imposters demanded the money on transit and Standard Chartered's ATM passwords